From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: senposage <onemoar@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 23 Mar 2026 00:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] feat: sv_smoothClients -- TR_LINEAR trajectory for smoother
 player rendering

Server-side snapshot rewriting that converts TR_INTERPOLATE player entities
to TR_LINEAR with position + velocity data.  The client extrapolates forward
between snapshots instead of snapping between discrete positions, producing
smooth continuous motion at any sv_fps.

New cvars:
  sv_smoothClients 0|1  -- enable TR_LINEAR trajectory rewriting (default 1)
  sv_velSmooth <ms>     -- EWA velocity smoothing window (default -1=auto)
                           -1 = 4 * frameMsec (e.g. 80 ms at sv_fps 50)
                            0 = off (raw per-tick velocity)

The velocity smoothing uses a per-client ring buffer (32 slots) with
exponential weighted average: the most-recent sample dominates (~53%
weight at 50 Hz / 80 ms window), older samples decay by half per step.
This eliminates per-tick trDelta jitter that manifests as blur or
micro-stutter for fast-moving players, without adding directional lag.

Implementation:
  - Ring buffer records origin + velocity each sv_fps tick
  - SV_SmoothRecordAll() called after GAME_RUN_FRAME in SV_Frame
  - Snapshot entity loop rewrites TR_INTERPOLATE -> TR_LINEAR for
    player entities with speed > ~10 ups (DotProduct > 100)
  - Idle players keep TR_INTERPOLATE with anchored trTime
  - Bots are excluded (they work correctly with TR_INTERPOLATE)
  - SV_SmoothClearClient() called on disconnect to prevent stale data
  - trTime anchored for all TR_INTERPOLATE client entities (needed for
    cgame QVM patches that redirect TR_INTERPOLATE -> TR_LINEAR)
  - es->origin synced to es->pos.trBase (fixes spot-shadow divergence)

Files modified:
  server.h      -- cvar externs + function prototypes
  sv_main.c     -- cvar definitions + SV_SmoothRecordAll call
  sv_init.c     -- cvar registration + SV_SmoothInit call
  sv_client.c   -- SV_SmoothClearClient on drop
  sv_snapshot.c -- ring buffer + snapshot entity rewriting

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
